#!ek9
<?-
  Literal Validation Fuzz Test: DateTime - Invalid Timezone Offset
  Tests if EK9 catches invalid timezone offset (+99:99) at compile time.

  Expected: Should fail (timezone offset must be valid, e.g., -12:00 to +14:00)
  Actual: Compiles successfully, becomes unset at runtime
-?>
defines module fuzz.literal.datetime.badtz
  defines program
    TestInvalidTimezone()
      dt <- 2024-01-15T12:00:00+99:99
      stdout <- Stdout()
      if dt?
        stdout.println("Set")
//EOF
